WEBVTT

00:01.208 --> 00:04.038
[arrows whooshing]

00:13.875 --> 00:18.880
[gentle piano music]
[birds chirping]

01:41.308 --> 01:43.241
- I can't be late.

01:43.275 --> 01:44.483
- You won't be.

01:48.453 --> 01:49.178
- What?

01:50.179 --> 01:51.007
- Nothing.

01:52.008 --> 01:53.941
[Pearl giggles]

01:53.975 --> 01:55.667
- I know you love me.

01:58.048 --> 02:01.121
[Pearl giggling]

02:01.155 --> 02:03.640
[gentle music]

02:06.540 --> 02:09.473
[Pearl] I wanna control my
destiny.

02:09.508 --> 02:13.133
- And how do you
envision achieving that?

02:13.167 --> 02:14.789
- I'm going to work hard,

02:14.824 --> 02:16.791
harder than anyone else.

02:16.826 --> 02:18.793
And I'll graduate with honors
and go to Harvard or Yale

02:18.828 --> 02:20.450
with a double major
in political science

02:20.485 --> 02:22.659
and global economics.

02:22.694 --> 02:24.144
I wanna intern at
the UN and one day

02:24.178 --> 02:26.456
be an ambassador to France.

02:26.491 --> 02:27.871
- [Betty] And why
do you think Winston

02:27.906 --> 02:29.977
is a good fit for Pearl?

02:30.011 --> 02:31.875
- A mixture of your
strong academics

02:31.910 --> 02:33.981
and the individual attention
you have for the girls

02:34.015 --> 02:37.157
makes you a wonderful
fit as you would say.

02:37.191 --> 02:39.469
- Well, Pearl is a
magnificent girl.

02:39.504 --> 02:43.301
A 4.4 GPA, eights and
nines on her ISEEs,

02:43.335 --> 02:44.854
an accomplished pianist,

02:44.888 --> 02:48.168
well-liked by her teachers,
popular with her friends.

02:48.202 --> 02:49.169
What's your secret?

02:49.203 --> 02:50.653
- Well, it takes a village.

02:50.687 --> 02:54.001
- A stable home is paramount
in creating Winston girls.

02:54.035 --> 02:55.313
If there's trouble in the house,

02:55.347 --> 02:58.316
there's very little we
can do to overcome it.

02:58.350 --> 02:59.351
Oh, this way.

03:01.698 --> 03:04.701
[people chattering]

03:08.222 --> 03:13.193
[clock chiming and ticking]
[tense music]

03:33.247 --> 03:34.214
[glass thuds]

03:34.248 --> 03:36.216
[Jack groaning]

03:36.250 --> 03:38.908
[ominous music]

03:41.393 --> 03:43.947
[Jack sighing]

03:48.918 --> 03:51.231
[Jack sighs]

03:55.407 --> 03:57.927
[Jack panting]

04:02.656 --> 04:03.553
[dark suspenseful music]

04:03.588 --> 04:05.072
- [Anthony] Oh I'm telling.

04:05.106 --> 04:06.556
What, you think I'm gonna
put up your whoring around?

04:06.591 --> 04:07.419
[rifle firing]

04:07.454 --> 04:08.731
- [Helen] Would you calm down?

04:08.765 --> 04:09.456
- [Anthony] Oh good,
'cause you don't want

04:09.490 --> 04:10.284
a whore, I'm unreal.

04:10.319 --> 04:11.251
- [Helen] Let it be.

04:11.285 --> 04:12.631
- Who was he?
- A guy.

04:12.666 --> 04:13.736
- [Anthony] Oh uh, you go
with the internet guy, right?

04:13.770 --> 04:15.082
[rifle firing]
[Pearl panting]

04:15.116 --> 04:16.255
- I wasn't with that guy.
- You fucked him!

04:16.290 --> 04:17.394
Now get away from--
[tense music]

04:17.428 --> 04:18.637
- [Anthony] No, you
fucked him, didn't ya?

04:18.672 --> 04:19.430
You fucked that
British guy Simon too.

04:19.466 --> 04:20.915
- I fucked 'em all

04:20.950 --> 04:23.090
because I need a man not a crazy drunk, emotional cripple.

04:23.124 --> 04:24.574
[rifle firing]

04:24.609 --> 04:25.748
[shell casing clattering]

04:25.782 --> 04:27.991
- Mom, Anthony?
[suspenseful music]

04:37.967 --> 04:41.281
[rifle clacking]

04:41.315 --> 04:42.282
[gasps] No.

04:45.630 --> 04:46.941
No.

04:46.976 --> 04:48.184
[rifle firing]

04:48.218 --> 04:53.223
[birds chirping]
[dog barking]

04:53.810 --> 04:56.157
[tense music]

05:05.166 --> 05:10.171
[suspenseful music]
[door clattering and creaking]

05:20.354 --> 05:21.321
- Oh my God.

05:24.013 --> 05:26.671
[Pearl crying]

05:48.382 --> 05:52.386
[police radio chattering]

05:52.421 --> 05:54.940
- [Officer] Were they married?

05:55.872 --> 05:56.701
- What?

05:57.943 --> 05:59.704
- We're they married?

06:04.260 --> 06:06.711
[Eve crying]

06:10.784 --> 06:13.614
[birds chirping]

06:27.594 --> 06:30.251
[somber music]

06:32.461 --> 06:35.774
[keys jangling]

06:35.809 --> 06:37.466
- Come on, Grandma.

06:38.432 --> 06:39.537
Let me help you up.

06:39.571 --> 06:40.400
Come on.

06:50.271 --> 06:52.998
[engine revving]

06:57.486 --> 07:00.350
[tires screeching]

07:34.315 --> 07:36.973
[phone ringing]

07:40.874 --> 07:43.532
[Jack groaning]

07:47.984 --> 07:49.883
- That was a new trick.

07:51.643 --> 07:52.679
- [Isaac] Jack Wolf?
- Yeah.

07:52.713 --> 07:54.197
- It's Isaac Robbins.

07:54.232 --> 07:57.822
We met years ago when you
were seeing Helen Rosen.

07:58.823 --> 07:59.548
- Right.

08:00.825 --> 08:01.826
You were um,

08:03.344 --> 08:04.518
her pal, a lawyer.

08:04.553 --> 08:06.796
- [Isaac] You sort of
swept her off her feet.

08:06.831 --> 08:08.177
- Yeah, it was mutual.

08:08.211 --> 08:11.663
- [Isaac] I'm
representing her estate.

08:11.698 --> 08:14.355
- [grunts] Her estate?

08:14.390 --> 08:16.668
- [Isaac] She's dead.

08:16.703 --> 08:18.877
She was killed last night.

08:20.223 --> 08:21.535
I'm sorry, Jack.

08:22.916 --> 08:26.195
- What do you mean killed,
how was she killed?

08:26.229 --> 08:28.162
- [Isaac] The funeral's Friday.

08:28.197 --> 08:30.371
Mountainview in Altadena, 10:00.

08:30.406 --> 08:32.650
I thought you'd wanna be there.

08:32.683 --> 08:35.653
- Do you know I haven't seen
her for many, many years.

08:35.687 --> 08:39.241
- [Isaac] It's important
that you be there.

08:41.037 --> 08:44.006
[Jack grunts]

08:44.039 --> 08:46.387
[Jack sighs]

08:52.048 --> 08:54.395
- You have to eat something.

09:02.611 --> 09:06.718
That policeman asked if
I was angry at my mother.

09:08.306 --> 09:10.722
- I don't know what happened.

09:13.242 --> 09:14.968
- They were fighting.

09:17.418 --> 09:19.559
And then Anthony shot Mom.

09:20.421 --> 09:22.492
And then he shot himself.

09:24.598 --> 09:26.566
- She shoulda...

09:26.600 --> 09:28.084
She can't be gone.

09:30.259 --> 09:32.123
She can't be gone.

09:32.157 --> 09:33.573
It's not possible.
[somber music]

09:36.265 --> 09:38.094
- I'm so sorry, Nana.

09:39.786 --> 09:41.132
- [Nana] I know.

09:48.518 --> 09:51.832
[gentle Parisian music]

09:59.840 --> 10:03.119
[police siren wailing]

10:04.500 --> 10:07.296
[engine revving]

10:10.782 --> 10:11.645
[car clattering]

10:11.680 --> 10:12.957
- Fuck!

10:12.991 --> 10:15.269
What the hell are you doing?

10:15.304 --> 10:16.443
- You just pulled out.
- You just come screaming

10:16.477 --> 10:17.168
down the street.
- You didn't even look.

10:17.202 --> 10:18.618
You have to look

10:18.652 --> 10:19.515
before you pull out.
- Could've killed somebody.

10:19.549 --> 10:20.447
- Look what you did to my car.

10:20.481 --> 10:21.448
- What I did to your car?

10:21.482 --> 10:23.484
What the fuck you did to my car?

10:27.005 --> 10:28.835
- I, I didn't see you.

10:29.801 --> 10:31.458
[sighs] I was upset--

10:31.492 --> 10:32.632
- No one lived.

10:32.666 --> 10:33.667
I don't think I was focused.

10:33.702 --> 10:34.944
I wasn't concentrating here.

10:34.979 --> 10:36.187
- No, it's my fault.

10:36.221 --> 10:37.464
I was speeding and I
wasn't paying attention

10:37.498 --> 10:39.777
and then suddenly
you were just there.

10:39.811 --> 10:42.331
[both sighing]

10:43.988 --> 10:44.989
Are you okay?

10:46.404 --> 10:47.198
- Yeah.

10:49.200 --> 10:50.477
You're American?

10:50.511 --> 10:51.512
- Obviously.

10:52.997 --> 10:54.964
- So what were you upset about?

10:54.999 --> 10:57.208
- [scoffs] My
husband just left me

10:57.242 --> 10:58.381
and I think it's my fault.

10:58.416 --> 10:59.486
I mean, I know it's my fault.

10:59.520 --> 11:00.211
- [Jack] Oh.

11:00.245 --> 11:01.143
- Helen.

11:01.177 --> 11:03.248
- Oh, uh, Jack, Jack Wolf.

11:07.183 --> 11:08.012
- I uh...

11:09.703 --> 11:10.531
Here.

11:11.532 --> 11:13.224
For insurance.

11:13.258 --> 11:14.501
- Right.

11:14.535 --> 11:17.815
Well, you know, it's
probably for the best.

11:17.849 --> 11:19.989
[police siren wailing]

11:20.024 --> 11:21.163
Your breakup.

11:21.197 --> 11:22.336
- Oh!

11:22.371 --> 11:24.407
That's what they always say.

11:24.442 --> 11:27.169
- Oh, I'm not so
sure about that.

11:27.203 --> 11:29.171
- Should I give you my number,

11:29.205 --> 11:30.034
I mean, for the car?
- Do you wanna,

11:30.068 --> 11:31.242
do you wanna have a drink?

11:31.276 --> 11:32.519
- What, you think I need one?

11:32.553 --> 11:34.901
- [chuckles] I know I do.

11:34.935 --> 11:36.350
- Uh [sighs].

11:36.385 --> 11:37.869
- I know, I,

11:37.904 --> 11:39.250
look I know you don't,

11:39.284 --> 11:40.009
[sighs] you don't know me
[gentle music]

11:40.044 --> 11:41.183
so I--

11:41.217 --> 11:42.840
- No, I know, I mean,
I don't know you

11:42.874 --> 11:45.049
but I can see you're kind.

11:50.295 --> 11:52.712
I don't belong here.

11:52.746 --> 11:54.023
I'm from LA.

11:54.058 --> 11:54.852
- Me too.

11:54.886 --> 11:56.094
West Hollywood.

11:57.578 --> 11:58.752
- Oh.

11:58.787 --> 12:00.720
I wanna go home.

12:00.754 --> 12:02.583
- I'll take you.

12:02.618 --> 12:03.446
I will.

12:04.758 --> 12:06.380
- We just met.

12:06.415 --> 12:08.797
- [Jack] How long were
you and Michele together?

12:11.075 --> 12:12.766
- [Helen] Seven years.

12:12.801 --> 12:14.734
- [Jack] Do you
think he knew you?

12:14.768 --> 12:15.596
- No.

12:17.909 --> 12:19.048
You married?

12:19.083 --> 12:20.394
- Mmm nnn.

12:20.429 --> 12:21.775
- Divorced?

12:21.810 --> 12:23.121
- Never married.

12:24.260 --> 12:26.884
- But you've been in love?

12:26.918 --> 12:27.747
- Uh...

12:30.646 --> 12:31.612
Yeah, once.

12:32.682 --> 12:36.238
- [sniffles] What was she like?

12:36.272 --> 12:37.757
- She was curious,

12:39.793 --> 12:40.829
smart, funny.

12:43.279 --> 12:44.073
- [Helen] She sounds sexy.

12:44.108 --> 12:45.247
- [Jack] Mmm hmm.

12:45.281 --> 12:47.767
- [Helen] Where is she?

12:47.801 --> 12:48.940
- Um, she's uh,

12:51.115 --> 12:52.495
she's right here.

12:54.290 --> 12:56.120
Yeah, she's right here.

13:07.131 --> 13:09.789
[food sizzling]

13:11.652 --> 13:12.792
- Oh.

13:12.826 --> 13:14.276
- [Pearl] Why
aren't you dressed?

13:14.310 --> 13:15.277
- I'm not going.

13:15.311 --> 13:16.623
- What do you mean?

13:16.657 --> 13:17.624
- [Eve] Enough.

13:17.658 --> 13:18.625
- You have to go!

13:18.659 --> 13:19.453
It's your daughter's funeral!

13:19.488 --> 13:20.523
- I'm not going!

13:20.558 --> 13:21.524
- You have to go, Nana!

13:21.559 --> 13:22.836
- My daughter is dead.

13:22.871 --> 13:24.493
What difference does it make?

13:24.527 --> 13:26.460
- You can't not go!

13:26.495 --> 13:29.360
[doorbell ringing]

13:30.982 --> 13:31.811
- Hi.

13:32.708 --> 13:34.365
You must be Pearl.

13:34.399 --> 13:36.298
I'm Isaac, Isaac Robbins.

13:36.332 --> 13:40.820
I'm an attorney and an old
friend of your mother's.

13:40.854 --> 13:43.063
I'm so sorry for your loss.

13:44.893 --> 13:45.894
- Thank you.

13:47.999 --> 13:49.656
- Well, I have a car
waiting to take you

13:49.690 --> 13:50.553
to the service.

13:50.588 --> 13:51.831
- Oh!

13:51.865 --> 13:54.557
This is all simply
too much to bear.

13:57.388 --> 13:59.321
[door clattering]

13:59.355 --> 14:00.874
[door thudding]

14:00.909 --> 14:03.704
- Did you know my
mother a long time?

14:03.739 --> 14:04.567
- Yes.

14:05.914 --> 14:07.087
I admired her.

14:10.366 --> 14:12.196
- Did you know my dad?

14:13.887 --> 14:14.715
- No.

14:17.063 --> 14:19.410
- He died before I was born.

14:24.933 --> 14:26.279
I'll go get her.

14:27.936 --> 14:30.904
[people chattering]

14:33.942 --> 14:36.392
[Eve crying]

14:40.224 --> 14:41.708
- [Man] I hear it's pretty good.

14:41.742 --> 14:43.883
- [Man] An old friend of yours.

14:43.917 --> 14:45.919
- [Woman] Hi, thought
you'd never make it.

14:45.954 --> 14:47.196
- [Isaac] Jack.

14:47.231 --> 14:48.094
- [Man] You got
a telephone here?

14:48.128 --> 14:49.440
- [Isaac] Been a long time.

14:49.474 --> 14:50.303
- Yeah.

14:51.407 --> 14:52.443
It has, um...

14:53.616 --> 14:55.929
Look, I appreciate
the invitation

14:55.964 --> 14:57.448
but I don't understand.

14:57.482 --> 14:58.898
- I couldn't say what I
have to say over the phone

14:58.932 --> 15:00.071
and there was no time.

15:00.106 --> 15:02.936
- Well, how much
time do you need?

15:14.120 --> 15:17.088
[people chuckling]

15:18.814 --> 15:21.058
[Jack inhales deeply]

15:21.092 --> 15:24.061
[Jack scoffs]

15:24.095 --> 15:24.958
- I don't think so.

15:24.993 --> 15:27.064
- It's authentic.

15:27.098 --> 15:28.410
- How long have you had this?

15:28.444 --> 15:30.757
- I just opened her safe
deposit box yesterday.

15:30.791 --> 15:32.759
- Yeah, but it's
addressed to you.

15:32.793 --> 15:34.934
- Helen trusted me.

15:34.968 --> 15:37.453
[gentle music]

15:40.284 --> 15:42.010
- Does the girl know?

15:48.464 --> 15:51.467
[people chattering]

16:01.477 --> 16:05.792
♪ Oh Mama, there's
a Spanish dancer ♪

16:05.826 --> 16:10.176
♪ Whose steps I follow
when he comes near ♪

16:10.210 --> 16:14.352
♪ The red dress of temptation

16:14.387 --> 16:19.012
♪ Over a long black
slip of fears ♪

16:19.047 --> 16:23.465
♪ Will I fall beneath the
shadow of some broken cross ♪

16:23.499 --> 16:24.466
♪ My arms emptied

16:24.500 --> 16:29.505
♪ And all my treasures lost

16:33.026 --> 16:37.548
♪ Still like that
Spanish dancer I ♪

16:37.582 --> 16:42.139
♪ Throw my roses down for him

16:42.173 --> 16:45.832
♪ Across these beds
of darkness he ♪

16:45.866 --> 16:50.871
♪ Opens his arms and
gathers them in ♪

16:52.770 --> 16:56.670
♪ Oh Mama, the
bridges were burning ♪

16:56.705 --> 17:01.158
♪ Over a river black and cold
[machine whirring]

17:01.192 --> 17:05.507
♪ But I walked when
love commanded me ♪

17:05.540 --> 17:09.406
♪ Up to the edges of his soul

17:09.442 --> 17:10.925
- Pearl.

17:10.960 --> 17:15.068
♪ But I'm still frightened
of that dark divide ♪

17:15.103 --> 17:19.797
♪ Oh, will I gain
entrance or be denied ♪

17:24.905 --> 17:26.183
[thunder cracking]

17:26.217 --> 17:27.701
- I want three.

17:27.736 --> 17:28.530
- Three?

17:28.564 --> 17:29.531
- Mmm hmm.

17:29.565 --> 17:31.533
My mom was one of three

17:31.567 --> 17:35.882
and I've always wanted
a brother and a sister.

17:35.916 --> 17:38.574
- You know, I don't think
I could handle three.

17:38.609 --> 17:41.577
I mean, having one
is tough enough.

17:45.098 --> 17:45.926
[rain pattering]

17:45.961 --> 17:48.481
- I think I'm gonna wander off.

17:49.930 --> 17:51.104
- Wander off?

17:51.139 --> 17:52.381
- Yeah.

17:52.416 --> 17:54.452
Meet you back here in an hour?
[gentle music]

17:54.487 --> 17:55.315
- Sure.

17:56.661 --> 17:57.490
- Okay.

18:02.253 --> 18:07.258
[tense music]
[thunder rumbling]

18:36.805 --> 18:39.635
[camera clicking]

18:46.815 --> 18:48.955
[police siren wailing]

18:48.989 --> 18:51.268
Do you love it here?

18:51.302 --> 18:53.132
- Thought I'd lost you.

18:55.720 --> 18:57.170
[Jack chuckles]

18:57.205 --> 18:58.309
- [Isaac] There's a problem
with the order of death.

18:58.344 --> 18:59.828
- What?

18:59.862 --> 19:00.967
- Well, it's better if we
discuss it in my office.

19:01.001 --> 19:02.279
- I'm not coming to your office.

19:02.313 --> 19:03.797
This has got nothing
to do with me.

19:03.832 --> 19:06.006
- Look, I don't want you
to be that girl's father.

19:06.041 --> 19:07.284
To be honest,
[people chattering]

19:07.318 --> 19:09.631
I don't understand what
Helen ever saw in you.

19:09.665 --> 19:11.288
And I wish to God I had
never opened that letter.

19:11.322 --> 19:12.185
Do you get that?

19:12.220 --> 19:13.152
- [Jack] Mmm hmm.

19:13.186 --> 19:14.325
- Okay.

19:14.360 --> 19:16.293
Helen left her entire
estate to her killer.

19:16.327 --> 19:17.984
We can get around that.

19:18.018 --> 19:21.056
But his family might contest
it and tie it up for years.

19:21.090 --> 19:21.884
- Why?

19:21.919 --> 19:22.989
- No, anger.

19:23.023 --> 19:24.163
- What are they angry about?

19:24.197 --> 19:25.992
- I don't know, maybe
they feel guilty.

19:26.026 --> 19:28.477
They don't wanna
accept responsibility.

19:28.512 --> 19:32.516
Times of tragedy, people
scurry away like mice.

19:33.689 --> 19:34.897
Will you take the girl?

19:34.932 --> 19:35.726
- What?

19:35.760 --> 19:37.210
- She's your daughter.

19:37.245 --> 19:41.352
- [chuckles] Helen never
told me anything about this.

19:41.387 --> 19:43.043
For all I know she
could be your daughter.

19:43.078 --> 19:45.218
- I was not Helen's lover.

19:46.875 --> 19:48.497
Can you support Pearl?

19:48.532 --> 19:49.671
- [Jack] I haven't even met her.

19:49.705 --> 19:51.017
- Do the math.

19:51.051 --> 19:52.674
Why would she choose
you if it weren't true?

19:52.708 --> 19:54.123
- I have no idea.

19:57.541 --> 19:59.405
Is that Helen's mother?

20:00.889 --> 20:01.717
- Yeah.

20:03.063 --> 20:05.514
- She doesn't look
too good right now.

20:05.549 --> 20:07.206
Look [sighs],

20:07.240 --> 20:09.518
I would make a poor
choice as guardian.

20:09.553 --> 20:11.520
- You're some sort of
artist, aren't you?

20:11.555 --> 20:12.728
- [Jack] Mmm.

20:13.557 --> 20:15.524
- They weren't actually married.

20:15.559 --> 20:17.768
His family doesn't want
that girl to see a penny.

20:17.802 --> 20:20.874
- Well, surely Helen
had money put away.

20:20.909 --> 20:22.221
You know, just in case.

20:22.255 --> 20:23.877
She was too smart not to.

20:23.912 --> 20:24.706
- I have no idea.

20:24.740 --> 20:25.948
- You were her lawyer.

20:25.983 --> 20:29.883
- She was in love and he
was a very wealthy man.

20:29.918 --> 20:31.713
She was in love.
[Jack sighs]

20:31.747 --> 20:34.578
- Yeah, and he
fucking killed her.

20:35.751 --> 20:38.720
[Kate inhaling deeply]
[birds chirping]

20:38.754 --> 20:41.101
- I can't live with my nana.

20:41.136 --> 20:43.897
[distant dog barking]

20:43.932 --> 20:45.071
- You should just live with us.

20:45.105 --> 20:46.590
My mom loves you.

20:46.624 --> 20:48.247
- [scoffs] Oh God yes.

20:48.281 --> 20:50.145
- We'd be like sisters.

20:51.595 --> 20:53.079
- Do you really think
it could happen?

20:53.113 --> 20:54.805
- I'm positive.

20:54.839 --> 20:56.289
I love you, Pearl.

20:57.601 --> 20:59.154
- I love you, Kate.

21:02.675 --> 21:03.572
- Oh, it's okay.

21:03.607 --> 21:05.919
You don't have to...

21:05.954 --> 21:07.576
Like that.

21:07.611 --> 21:08.439
Hi, I'm...

21:10.303 --> 21:11.270
My name is Jack.

21:11.304 --> 21:13.617
I just wanted to come over

21:13.651 --> 21:15.757
and offer my condolences.

21:15.791 --> 21:16.999
- Thanks, Jack.

21:17.034 --> 21:18.346
You knew my mom?

21:19.450 --> 21:20.279
- Yeah.

21:21.141 --> 21:23.178
Yeah, I did, a long time ago.

21:23.212 --> 21:26.146
- Well, it was nice
of you to come.

21:34.465 --> 21:35.984
- Um, yeah, sorry.

21:37.330 --> 21:39.332
Uh, thank you, thank you.

21:43.163 --> 21:46.891
- [scoffs] So fucking weird.

21:53.829 --> 21:56.315
[Eva snoring]

21:59.352 --> 22:02.182
[glasses clinking]

22:09.051 --> 22:11.709
[Isaac sighing]

22:13.711 --> 22:14.540
- What?

22:17.681 --> 22:20.856
- Do you wanna live
with your grandmother?

22:20.891 --> 22:24.826
Because I'm concerned she
can't take care of you.

22:24.860 --> 22:25.861
- She can't.

22:27.691 --> 22:30.487
- I wanna live with Kate
Siegel and her parents.

22:30.521 --> 22:33.041
- Do you think they
would take you?

22:33.075 --> 22:33.904
- Yes.

22:35.215 --> 22:37.356
They really care about me.

22:38.564 --> 22:41.532
- Well, it's a huge
responsibility.

22:42.602 --> 22:46.054
Did they tell you
they would foster you?

22:46.088 --> 22:46.917
- Not yet.

22:50.714 --> 22:51.508
I can't live
[tense music]

22:51.542 --> 22:53.233
with my grandmother.

23:09.974 --> 23:12.218
[gun clicking]

23:12.252 --> 23:13.046
[Jack grunts]

23:13.081 --> 23:14.254
[loud knocking]

23:14.289 --> 23:15.117
- Fuck!

23:17.430 --> 23:20.226
[panting] Go away!

23:20.260 --> 23:21.917
[loud knocking]

23:21.952 --> 23:23.781
[gun clattering]

23:23.816 --> 23:24.989
What the fuck?

23:34.447 --> 23:36.932
[Jack sighs]

23:40.764 --> 23:41.558
- Hi.

23:41.592 --> 23:42.593
- [Jack] Hi.

23:43.594 --> 23:44.940
Please come in.

23:54.674 --> 23:56.124
- What do you do?

23:57.608 --> 23:59.334
- Little of this,
a little of that.

23:59.368 --> 24:00.162
Please.

24:10.379 --> 24:12.140
[Jack sighs]

24:12.174 --> 24:13.175
- Filmmaker?

24:14.038 --> 24:15.454
- Yes.

24:15.488 --> 24:17.145
- Photographer?

24:17.179 --> 24:18.008
- Yep.

24:22.530 --> 24:24.048
- [Pearl] Painter?

24:27.224 --> 24:29.468
- What do you want?

24:29.502 --> 24:30.779
- What do you mean?

24:30.814 --> 24:31.780
- Coffee, tea?

24:31.815 --> 24:32.609
You drink coffee?

24:32.643 --> 24:33.989
- Do you have espresso?

24:34.024 --> 24:35.474
- [Jack] Yes.

24:35.508 --> 24:38.304
- I'll have tea, Earl Gray.

24:38.338 --> 24:39.478
- I have that.

24:46.001 --> 24:47.520
- [Pearl] So what
do you do here?

24:47.555 --> 24:49.349
- Uh, mostly I write.

24:50.558 --> 24:51.835
- What do you write?

24:51.869 --> 24:52.870
- Um, films.

24:54.838 --> 24:56.391
Essays, journals.

24:56.425 --> 24:58.358
- [Pearl] Do you sell anything?

24:58.393 --> 25:00.326
- I have sold things
from time to time

25:00.360 --> 25:01.810
but mostly I write for myself.

25:01.845 --> 25:04.675
[kettle whistling]

25:12.027 --> 25:12.856
- Thanks.

25:19.379 --> 25:20.380
Are you my father?

25:20.415 --> 25:21.830
- Why would you ask me that?

25:21.865 --> 25:23.660
- You were dating my mother
when she got pregnant.

25:23.694 --> 25:24.902
- [Jack] She didn't tell
me she was pregnant.

25:24.937 --> 25:29.044
- [scoffs] You're
not sure, are you?

25:29.079 --> 25:31.219
What if you're my father?

25:44.404 --> 25:45.578
You could be my father.

25:45.613 --> 25:47.028
- You don't want me
to be your father.

25:47.062 --> 25:47.891
- No.

25:50.238 --> 25:51.860
- So what do you want?

25:51.895 --> 25:53.413
- Kate Siegel is my best
friend and her parents

25:53.448 --> 25:54.863
want to adopt me.

25:54.898 --> 25:56.589
Her dad's the head of
a big talent agency.

25:56.624 --> 25:58.384
- What, Marty Siegel?

25:58.418 --> 25:59.868
- [Pearl] You know him?

25:59.903 --> 26:02.595
- Um, he's one of the top
agents in TV packaging

26:02.630 --> 26:03.907
in Los Angeles.

26:05.080 --> 26:08.049
- [Pearl] It's
what's best for me.

26:08.083 --> 26:09.222
- Why?

26:09.257 --> 26:10.879
- The Siegels know everyone.

26:10.914 --> 26:13.882
They go everywhere, stay
at the very best places.

26:13.917 --> 26:15.746
They would protect me.

26:17.092 --> 26:19.612
This is how my mom
would've raised me.

26:19.647 --> 26:22.097
So my thought is if
you're my legal guardian,

26:22.132 --> 26:24.893
you could say I'm meant
to be living with them.

26:24.928 --> 26:28.241
- Does your grandmother
know about this?

26:28.276 --> 26:29.967
She's not on board
with this, is she?

26:30.002 --> 26:31.072
She wants you to live with her.

26:31.106 --> 26:31.935
- I can't.

26:33.108 --> 26:34.247
- [Jack] You could
take care of her.

26:34.282 --> 26:36.249
- I love her but I can't.

26:36.284 --> 26:38.148
[Jack sighs]

26:38.182 --> 26:41.323
- Did Robbins give
you my address?

26:41.358 --> 26:42.601
Oh, and you thought
it was better

26:42.635 --> 26:46.328
to just come here rather
than call me first.

26:46.363 --> 26:47.951
[Jack sighing]

26:47.985 --> 26:50.332
You see the letter?

26:50.367 --> 26:52.162
- He showed me a copy.

26:52.196 --> 26:54.302
- [Jack] And you still
think I'm your father?

26:54.336 --> 26:55.614
- Does it matter?

26:55.648 --> 26:57.650
You don't want a kid and
I have somewhere to go.

26:57.685 --> 26:58.927
- Wow.

26:58.962 --> 27:00.619
Practical girl.

27:00.653 --> 27:01.827
- [Pearl] All you have to do

27:01.861 --> 27:03.276
is have a paternity
test and claim me.

27:03.311 --> 27:05.934
- And hand you over
to the Siegels?

27:05.969 --> 27:07.833
- I'm sure they'd
be appreciative.

27:07.867 --> 27:10.352
Maybe he can help
you find a job.

27:10.387 --> 27:12.320
[Jack chuckling]

27:12.354 --> 27:13.493
What?

27:13.528 --> 27:14.805
Why shouldn't you
benefit from helping me?

27:14.840 --> 27:17.118
- Jesus, how old are you?

27:17.152 --> 27:20.017
- Do this for my
mom who you loved.

27:21.156 --> 27:23.642
[Pearl sighs]

27:27.680 --> 27:29.993
Just sign this for me please.

27:31.511 --> 27:32.789
It says you're my
guardian and you agree

27:32.823 --> 27:34.135
my life would be
better if I lived

27:34.169 --> 27:36.516
with Sunny and Marty Siegel.

27:42.730 --> 27:45.215
[Jack groans]

27:51.014 --> 27:51.808
- This is what you want?

27:51.842 --> 27:53.395
- This is what I want.

27:53.430 --> 27:55.397
- I'm pretty sure
I'm not your father.

27:55.432 --> 27:58.090
- My grandmother's an alcoholic.

28:01.749 --> 28:04.199
[Jack sighs]

28:16.902 --> 28:17.730
Thank you.

28:22.045 --> 28:22.873
- Pearl.

28:25.738 --> 28:26.566
Good luck.

28:27.740 --> 28:29.190
- You too.

28:29.224 --> 28:32.572
[gentle Parisian music]

28:40.580 --> 28:43.411
[camera clicking]

28:45.620 --> 28:48.416
[swans quacking]

28:52.282 --> 28:55.112
[camera clicking]

28:58.771 --> 29:02.602
[speaking in foreign language]

29:07.642 --> 29:10.265
[Jack grunts]

29:10.300 --> 29:12.751
- I think I got a crush on you.

29:12.785 --> 29:13.924
- I know.

29:13.959 --> 29:16.237
- Oh, you're pretty
cocky, aren't you?

29:16.271 --> 29:18.929
[Jack chuckles]

29:20.310 --> 29:22.968
[Jack groaning]

29:27.110 --> 29:27.938
Oh.

29:32.287 --> 29:34.945
[Jack grunting]

29:42.850 --> 29:45.818
- [Eve] I can't believe
you found that loser.

29:45.853 --> 29:47.095
It'll never hold up in court.

29:47.130 --> 29:48.787
- My mom wanted him
to be my guardian.

29:48.821 --> 29:51.134
He's my father and he
gave his permission.

29:51.168 --> 29:53.136
- He's not your father.

29:54.033 --> 29:54.827
It doesn't matter.

29:54.862 --> 29:55.724
- Why?

29:57.657 --> 29:59.659
- Because the Siegels
don't want you.

29:59.694 --> 30:00.971
- Yes, they do.

30:01.834 --> 30:04.112
- I spoke to the mother, Bunny.

30:04.147 --> 30:05.113
- Sunny.

30:05.148 --> 30:06.218
She loves me.

30:07.875 --> 30:11.810
- They feel that you need
special care right now.

30:11.844 --> 30:15.952
Given the exigencies of
Martin's responsibilities

30:15.986 --> 30:17.160
at the agency,

30:18.506 --> 30:20.301
the household couldn't really
[gentle music]

30:20.335 --> 30:24.477
withstand the changes that
taking on another child,

30:24.512 --> 30:26.997
especially one with
special needs would bring.

30:27.032 --> 30:28.343
- You're lying.

30:32.209 --> 30:33.176
[tense music]

30:33.210 --> 30:34.039
[phone beeping]

30:34.073 --> 30:34.867
Call Kay.

30:38.181 --> 30:39.182
- [Kate] Yo, it's Kate.

30:39.216 --> 30:40.010
You know what to do.

30:40.045 --> 30:40.873
[phone beeps]

30:40.908 --> 30:42.254
- Please call me.

30:47.880 --> 30:49.986
- Face it, kiddo.

30:50.020 --> 30:51.263
I'm all you got.

31:03.378 --> 31:04.172
[door clattering]

31:04.207 --> 31:06.865
[food sizzling]

31:09.557 --> 31:11.697
- Don't you lock your door?

31:11.731 --> 31:12.560
- No.

31:15.045 --> 31:16.909
- My grandmother poisoned
their minds against me.

31:16.944 --> 31:18.393
- Who?

31:18.428 --> 31:20.085
The Siegels?

31:20.119 --> 31:21.707
Marty Siegel?

31:21.741 --> 31:24.020
- They don't want me.

31:24.054 --> 31:24.883
- [Jack] He's an asshole.

31:24.917 --> 31:26.712
- No, he's not.

31:26.746 --> 31:27.575
- Yeah.

31:28.576 --> 31:29.888
He's an asshole.

31:31.406 --> 31:32.200
- [Pearl] Can I stay here?

31:32.235 --> 31:33.615
- No.

31:33.650 --> 31:34.893
- Just until I can reach
Kate and straighten this out.

31:34.927 --> 31:35.894
- No.

31:35.928 --> 31:37.033
- You don't have
to be my father.

31:37.067 --> 31:38.206
- If I'm not your
father, then I'm guilty

31:38.241 --> 31:39.552
of kidnapping a minor.

31:39.587 --> 31:40.726
- No one would prosecute you.

31:40.760 --> 31:42.279
- Your grandmother.

31:46.939 --> 31:48.389
[phone beeps]

31:48.423 --> 31:49.769
- Hey, Mr. Robbins.

31:49.804 --> 31:51.047
Pearl Rosen.

31:51.081 --> 31:52.565
Can you talk with my dad

31:52.600 --> 31:54.291
or the guy who might be my dad.

31:54.326 --> 31:55.741
I need to assure him
he won't go to prison

31:55.775 --> 31:58.951
if I crash on his
couch for a few days.

32:00.780 --> 32:01.747
Oh.

32:01.781 --> 32:02.817
I'm actually here right now.

32:02.851 --> 32:04.577
- Nope.
- One second.

32:04.612 --> 32:06.786
- I don't wanna talk to...

32:08.512 --> 32:11.274
[Jack grunts]

32:11.308 --> 32:12.137
Yeah.

32:15.105 --> 32:18.143
Yeah, but I'm not her father.

32:18.177 --> 32:21.525
Yeah, without my
knowledge 15 years ago.

32:23.113 --> 32:23.942
Uh huh.

32:25.357 --> 32:30.258
Well, I'm still not gonna
say that I'm her father.

32:30.293 --> 32:31.466
Yeah, you too.

32:36.126 --> 32:38.542
- You have that old
sports car, don't you?

32:41.028 --> 32:43.685
[door thudding]

32:44.721 --> 32:47.966
[distant dog barking]

32:48.000 --> 32:50.347
- Come back here,
you little thief!

32:50.382 --> 32:52.004
I know you took my money!

32:52.039 --> 32:53.454
- I didn't take your money!

32:53.488 --> 32:54.662
- Help me!
- It's my money.

32:54.696 --> 32:56.284
- I'm being robbed!
- She seems upset.

32:56.319 --> 32:57.285
- Police!

32:57.320 --> 32:59.011
- Call you tomorrow, Nana.

32:59.046 --> 33:00.288
Go.

33:00.323 --> 33:02.808
- Come back here with
my child, you crook,

33:02.842 --> 33:04.879
you goddamn crook.

33:04.913 --> 33:07.502
[gentle music]

33:39.879 --> 33:40.880
- I love you.

33:42.882 --> 33:44.056
[people chattering]

33:44.091 --> 33:44.919
- What?

33:46.058 --> 33:46.886
- Nothin'.

33:48.233 --> 33:50.718
[Jack laughing]

33:50.752 --> 33:52.030
- I make you happy.

33:52.064 --> 33:52.892
- Yeah.

34:01.384 --> 34:02.937
[Jack groans]

34:02.971 --> 34:04.870
- [Pearl] When will
you know the results?

34:04.904 --> 34:05.698
- I'm not sure.

34:05.733 --> 34:07.045
Next week maybe.

34:10.219 --> 34:11.911
- Where are you gonna sleep?

34:11.946 --> 34:14.085
- Downstairs on the couch.

34:15.225 --> 34:16.192
I sleep there often.

34:16.226 --> 34:17.054
It's fine.

34:17.089 --> 34:19.228
[metal clanking]

34:19.264 --> 34:20.368
- What's that?

34:20.402 --> 34:21.989
- It's the mailbox.

34:23.820 --> 34:25.201
Mail comes through
right in the house.

34:25.235 --> 34:26.098
It's, uh...

34:28.411 --> 34:29.274
old school.

34:52.297 --> 34:54.782
[Jack sighs]

34:56.784 --> 34:57.612
Pearl.

35:00.512 --> 35:02.100
This one's for you.

35:08.796 --> 35:11.868
[footsteps clacking]

35:17.839 --> 35:20.463
[gentle music]

35:37.307 --> 35:39.137
[gentle knocking]

35:39.171 --> 35:39.999
Pearl.

35:45.004 --> 35:47.662
[Pearl crying]

35:51.494 --> 35:54.013
[tense music]

36:02.919 --> 36:03.989
Hi.

36:04.023 --> 36:05.818
I'm Jack Wolf and this is Pearl

36:05.853 --> 36:09.546
and I was wondering if we
could see Ms. Whetstone.

36:09.581 --> 36:10.996
- Is she expecting you?

36:11.030 --> 36:11.824
- We don't have an appointment
but it's important.

36:11.859 --> 36:14.206
[door clattering]

36:14.241 --> 36:15.483
Sorry to barge in.

36:15.518 --> 36:17.554
- No, no, please come in.

36:23.388 --> 36:25.838
Mr. Robbins called.

36:25.873 --> 36:30.705
And may I say how terribly
sorry we all are for your loss.

36:30.740 --> 36:32.224
- Thank you.

36:32.259 --> 36:34.364
- How are you feeling, Pearl?

36:34.399 --> 36:36.021
- I'm okay, thank you.

36:36.055 --> 36:37.022
- You know, under
the circumstances

36:37.056 --> 36:39.680
she's doing incredibly well.

36:39.714 --> 36:43.511
- Mr. Robbins explained that
you're her birth father.

36:43.546 --> 36:44.409
- Yeah.

36:46.549 --> 36:50.380
I only recently came
into Pearl's life.

36:50.415 --> 36:52.865
- And you're here to
discuss the letter.

36:52.900 --> 36:55.523
- No, I wanted to tell you
that there's no problem

36:55.558 --> 36:57.076
on paying the tuition,

36:57.111 --> 36:57.905
full-time.
- Mr. Wolf,

36:57.939 --> 36:59.424
it's not about money.

36:59.458 --> 37:02.599
- But my grades, my
community service.

37:03.566 --> 37:04.532
- I'm going to be frank.

37:04.567 --> 37:05.395
- Please.

37:06.948 --> 37:09.227
- Despite our
reputation for rigor,

37:09.261 --> 37:11.608
we want our girls to succeed.

37:11.643 --> 37:15.578
And Pearl has gone through
an incredible trauma.

37:15.612 --> 37:17.269
We felt the Winston program

37:17.304 --> 37:18.788
would only add to her stress.

37:18.822 --> 37:19.961
- [Jack] Don't you
think that's a question

37:19.996 --> 37:21.411
you should ask
Pearl or her family?

37:21.446 --> 37:25.588
- Honestly, we felt your
plate was terribly full.

37:26.934 --> 37:30.731
I know how disappointing
this must be for you, Pearl,

37:30.765 --> 37:34.390
but I sincerely believe that
this is what's best for you

37:34.424 --> 37:35.460
at this time.

37:36.461 --> 37:37.462
- Please.

37:37.496 --> 37:38.601
- I am sorry.

37:40.292 --> 37:42.260
- I don't think you are.

37:43.468 --> 37:44.296
Pearl.

37:51.441 --> 37:52.270
[door clattering]

37:52.304 --> 37:53.409
Can I come in?

37:53.443 --> 37:54.755
- You need to ask before
you open the door.

37:54.789 --> 37:56.274
- Oh, I'm sorry.

37:56.308 --> 37:57.102
You busy?

37:57.136 --> 37:58.310
- [Pearl] Yeah.

37:58.345 --> 37:59.311
- Well, put a pin
in your social media

37:59.346 --> 38:00.105
'cause we need to talk.

38:00.139 --> 38:00.933
- No, we don't.

38:00.968 --> 38:02.107
- Yeah.

38:02.141 --> 38:03.108
I'm sorry about Winston.

38:03.142 --> 38:04.420
- Go away!

38:04.454 --> 38:05.455
- We need to talk
about your school.

38:05.490 --> 38:06.491
- Winston is my school.

38:06.525 --> 38:07.837
- I've enrolled you into JB.

38:07.871 --> 38:09.114
- What's that?

38:09.148 --> 38:10.322
- John Burrows, it's
a local public school.

38:10.357 --> 38:11.289
- I'm not going
to public school!

38:11.323 --> 38:12.773
- Yeah, you are.

38:12.807 --> 38:13.946
You are going to public
school at least for this term.

38:13.981 --> 38:14.775
- You can't stop me!

38:14.809 --> 38:15.948
Winston is my school!

38:15.983 --> 38:17.122
I'm not going there!

38:17.156 --> 38:18.123
- It's not your fucking
school now, is it?

38:18.157 --> 38:19.297
- God, I hate you!

38:19.331 --> 38:21.816
It shoulda been you that died!

38:28.375 --> 38:30.825
[Jack sighs]

38:32.344 --> 38:35.071
- I know that you
don't trust me.

38:39.731 --> 38:42.837
But it's the best
I can do right now.

38:44.667 --> 38:48.843
It's gonna be okay.
[gentle music]

38:49.844 --> 38:52.260
[Jack sighs]

38:54.849 --> 38:57.162
- [Pearl] Why didn't
you tell me about him?

38:57.196 --> 39:00.993
He had a father and a
mother but they're all gone.

39:01.028 --> 39:04.342
She was pretty with
red hair like mine.

39:06.274 --> 39:08.035
He looks like his dad

39:09.277 --> 39:10.589
with those ears.

39:14.041 --> 39:16.871
Are all those people
related to me?

39:20.047 --> 39:23.050
My God, where did
he get those ears?

39:28.573 --> 39:29.401
- Do you want me to come in?

39:29.436 --> 39:30.678
- No.

39:30.713 --> 39:33.888
- Not even to say
hi to the principal?

39:36.408 --> 39:37.582
All right, I'll pick
you up after school.

39:37.616 --> 39:39.100
- We live six blocks away.

39:39.135 --> 39:41.862
Go write or whatever you do.

39:41.896 --> 39:42.725
- Okay.

39:49.421 --> 39:51.285
- So library's over there.

39:51.319 --> 39:52.700
[people chattering]

39:52.735 --> 39:54.875
And then the science building's
next to the parking lot.

39:54.909 --> 39:56.532
You can smoke there.

39:56.566 --> 39:57.912
- I don't smoke.

39:59.983 --> 40:01.399
- What are you lookin' at?

40:01.433 --> 40:03.401
- You I guess.

40:03.435 --> 40:05.437
- Don't be lookin' at me.

40:05.472 --> 40:07.405
Don't you ever be lookin' at me.

40:07.439 --> 40:08.613
- I thought you
were looking at me.

40:08.647 --> 40:12.548
- [chuckles] Why would
I be lookin' at you?

40:12.582 --> 40:13.756
- I don't know.

40:13.790 --> 40:15.723
I didn't wanna be
rude by looking away.

40:15.758 --> 40:18.416
- You didn't wanna be rude.
[girls chuckling]

40:18.450 --> 40:20.452
So you stare right at me?

40:20.487 --> 40:21.315
- I'm Pearl.

40:21.349 --> 40:22.350
- She's new.

40:23.662 --> 40:25.906
- Are you here for the
Special Ed program?

40:25.940 --> 40:27.425
[girls giggling]

40:27.459 --> 40:29.461
Are you special?

40:29.496 --> 40:31.429
- No, just trying
to be friendly.

40:31.463 --> 40:33.154
- Okay, we should go.

40:34.501 --> 40:37.918
- You're an interesting
girl, Perlita.

40:37.952 --> 40:39.126
- So are you.

40:39.160 --> 40:39.954
- Silvia.

40:41.128 --> 40:43.302
- That's a beautiful name.

40:49.654 --> 40:53.036
- [Student] Are you
brave or just stupid?

40:56.488 --> 40:57.765
[people chattering]
[rain pattering]

40:57.800 --> 41:01.148
- So how come a big-time
Hollywood director

41:01.182 --> 41:02.770
wants to teach
Film Directing One

41:02.805 --> 41:04.841
at an art school?

41:04.876 --> 41:06.291
- I just wanted to teach.

41:06.325 --> 41:07.119
- Uh huh.

41:07.154 --> 41:08.604
Why now?

41:08.638 --> 41:09.950
- You know, I've
been very fortunate

41:09.984 --> 41:12.608
so I thought it was
time to give back.

41:12.642 --> 41:13.471
- Uh huh.

41:14.506 --> 41:16.957
I talked to your agents,

41:16.991 --> 41:17.992
your former agents.

41:18.027 --> 41:19.822
They said that you're a pariah.

41:19.856 --> 41:21.133
Nobody wants to work with you.

41:21.168 --> 41:21.962
[Jack scoffs]

41:21.996 --> 41:23.688
Why is that, Jack?

41:23.722 --> 41:26.484
- Uh, 'cause I got a big mouth.

41:26.518 --> 41:27.830
Not proud of it.

41:29.348 --> 41:32.490
- So the big shot gets his
comeuppance, is that it?

41:32.524 --> 41:33.629
- I'm not a big shot.

41:33.663 --> 41:35.631
I'm just good at what I do.

41:35.665 --> 41:38.634
- Well, it's a basic course.

41:38.668 --> 41:39.876
It's not artsy.

41:41.844 --> 41:44.329
You ever teach before?

41:44.363 --> 41:46.365
We don't need an auteur.

41:49.092 --> 41:52.337
You know, you're thinking I
don't have to teach for a living

41:52.371 --> 41:55.823
and that, you know, I'm
betting if a slot opens up

41:55.858 --> 41:58.516
at "Gray's Anatomy", you'll
be outta here like a shot.

41:58.550 --> 42:00.034
- That is not true.

42:01.588 --> 42:05.177
- You're here as a
favor to Isaac Robbins.

42:05.212 --> 42:06.351
He's a decent man.

42:06.385 --> 42:09.009
He's never asked a
favor of me in 15 years.

42:09.043 --> 42:11.183
I told him you probably
wouldn't take the job

42:11.218 --> 42:15.118
and if you did, you'd be
outta here in a month.

42:16.395 --> 42:17.742
- When do I start?

42:17.776 --> 42:20.399
[upbeat music]

42:23.057 --> 42:23.886
- Hello?

42:34.621 --> 42:37.865
♪ You know I got a
string of kisses ♪

42:37.900 --> 42:40.040
♪ Tattooed down my arm

42:40.074 --> 42:42.042
♪ From the love of lonely men

42:42.076 --> 42:44.423
♪ That always came to harm

42:44.458 --> 42:46.564
♪ Tattooed down my arm

42:46.598 --> 42:48.600
♪ To my fingertips

42:48.635 --> 42:50.706
♪ You ain't the only lonely

42:50.740 --> 42:53.225
♪ Man that I've ever kissed
[register beeps and whirs]

42:53.260 --> 42:57.402
♪ But when the night
is sinking low ♪

42:57.436 --> 42:59.956
♪ Hold me oh

42:59.991 --> 43:01.475
♪ Here we go

43:01.509 --> 43:05.065
♪ When you turn that
charm light on me ♪

43:05.099 --> 43:06.307
- Need help?

43:06.342 --> 43:07.239
♪ Yeah, you turn
- No, it's okay

43:07.274 --> 43:08.482
♪ All the wrong

43:08.516 --> 43:10.070
♪ In my world right

43:10.104 --> 43:11.589
♪ When you turn
- Maybe.

43:11.623 --> 43:12.762
♪ That charm light on me

43:12.797 --> 43:14.108
- His name is Zack
and he's way old

43:14.143 --> 43:16.421
But I think he liked me.

43:16.455 --> 43:17.940
I don't know if he
liked me that way

43:17.974 --> 43:19.976
but we made a connection.

43:20.011 --> 43:22.427
Is that too dumb to say?

43:22.461 --> 43:23.255
I don't know.

43:23.290 --> 43:24.636
Should I buy this?

43:24.671 --> 43:25.499
- Yeah.

43:28.640 --> 43:30.918
- [Pearl] And he
gave me a record.

43:30.953 --> 43:31.747
[doorbell tinkling]

43:31.781 --> 43:33.921
♪ Ooh ooh

43:33.956 --> 43:36.096
♪ Ooh ooh

43:36.130 --> 43:38.443
♪ Ooh ooh ooh

43:38.477 --> 43:39.306
- Wow.

43:44.311 --> 43:45.795
How'd it go today?

43:50.179 --> 43:51.456
Kids okay?

43:51.490 --> 43:52.319
- Yeah.

43:53.492 --> 43:54.390
- Teachers?

43:57.807 --> 43:58.636
Homework?

43:59.706 --> 44:00.499
- No.

44:00.534 --> 44:01.639
Wine?

44:01.673 --> 44:03.641
- You're too young.

44:03.675 --> 44:04.849
- For you.

44:04.883 --> 44:05.712
- Ah.

44:07.023 --> 44:08.335
How did you um,

44:09.198 --> 44:11.821
how'd you learn to do all this?

44:13.547 --> 44:14.997
Oh yeah, she was,

44:16.170 --> 44:17.309
she was a great cook.

44:17.344 --> 44:18.966
- When she was inspired.

44:19.001 --> 44:20.209
- Yeah, well...

44:21.417 --> 44:23.143
I don't really believe
in inspiration.

44:23.177 --> 44:24.834
I think that you
get up every day

44:24.869 --> 44:29.494
and you go to work and you
do the best that you can.

44:29.528 --> 44:30.357
Mmm.

44:32.186 --> 44:34.361
This is fucking fantastic.

44:40.022 --> 44:41.023
I got a job.

44:44.854 --> 44:46.580
- When do you leave?

44:46.614 --> 44:48.686
- I'm not going anywhere.

44:49.583 --> 44:50.377
It's here in LA.

44:50.411 --> 44:51.896
I'm teaching.

44:51.930 --> 44:53.863
- What will you teach?

44:53.898 --> 44:55.382
- Film directing.

44:56.452 --> 44:58.626
But dean already hates me.

44:59.869 --> 45:01.733
- [chuckles] That
didn't take long.

45:01.768 --> 45:03.183
- Well, I didn't do anything.

45:03.217 --> 45:04.218
It's just...

45:05.392 --> 45:06.876
He hates who I am.

45:09.568 --> 45:10.915
Some people hate
you for who you are

45:10.949 --> 45:13.711
and some people hate you
for who they think you are.

45:13.745 --> 45:14.919
- You're paranoid.

45:14.953 --> 45:15.920
- Uh uh.

45:15.954 --> 45:16.955
He hates me.

45:18.094 --> 45:19.371
You know how I know?

45:19.406 --> 45:20.579
- [Pearl] How?

45:22.133 --> 45:23.237
- He told me.

45:25.481 --> 45:27.863
- [chuckles] He told
you he hates you?

45:27.897 --> 45:29.036
- Uh huh.

45:29.071 --> 45:31.798
He hates every single
thing about me.

45:39.426 --> 45:41.428
- Why do you have a gun?

45:46.778 --> 45:47.952
- Sometimes I just--

45:47.986 --> 45:49.056
- Think about killing yourself.

45:49.091 --> 45:49.919
- No.

45:54.441 --> 45:56.063
I got rid of it.

45:56.098 --> 45:57.755
- [Pearl] When?

45:57.789 --> 45:59.342
- When you moved in.

46:00.274 --> 46:01.103
- Really?

46:01.931 --> 46:03.277
- Yeah, really.

46:04.278 --> 46:05.107
- Good.

46:11.665 --> 46:13.598
- What's this?

46:13.632 --> 46:14.944
- An invitation.

46:18.706 --> 46:20.329
- Ah, Kate Siegel.

46:20.363 --> 46:22.434
That's good, yeah?

46:22.469 --> 46:23.297
- Read it.

46:27.163 --> 46:29.994
- Hmm, they want
to invite me too.

46:31.478 --> 46:33.342
- Her dad remembers you.

46:33.376 --> 46:34.481
- [Jack] Hmm.

46:38.381 --> 46:39.969
- Will you take me?

46:47.839 --> 46:48.875
- Yeah, sure.

46:55.847 --> 46:58.332
[gentle music]

47:02.716 --> 47:03.821
- It's for Kate's party.

47:03.855 --> 47:05.132
What do you think?

47:05.167 --> 47:07.307
- You look amazing.

47:07.341 --> 47:10.689
- [chuckles] I have two others.

47:10.724 --> 47:12.036
- Let's see 'em.

47:13.589 --> 47:16.316
[Pearl chuckles]

47:16.350 --> 47:19.146
- Could be a bit longer, maybe.

47:19.181 --> 47:20.838
Just below the knee.

47:22.046 --> 47:23.392
I'm just sayin'.

47:25.187 --> 47:27.534
- [Pearl] I haven't
seen Kate in weeks.

47:27.568 --> 47:30.848
Since you died, people
have avoided me.

47:32.021 --> 47:33.851
It's like I'm damaged.

47:34.782 --> 47:37.164
I have to show her I'm okay.

47:37.199 --> 47:39.718
I have to show all of
them I'm doing well,

47:39.753 --> 47:41.755
that I'm strong.
[people chattering]

47:45.379 --> 47:47.347
♪ Uh uh uh oh

47:47.381 --> 47:48.866
♪ Oh oh oh oh

47:48.900 --> 47:50.246
♪ You're one in a million

47:50.281 --> 47:52.559
♪ A million colors
a million shapes ♪

47:52.593 --> 47:55.907
♪ Whoa oh oh oh oh oh oh oh oh

47:55.942 --> 47:57.426
♪ You're one in a million

47:57.460 --> 47:59.877
♪ You're one in a million

47:59.911 --> 48:01.188
♪ Take your time

48:01.223 --> 48:02.880
♪ No apologies are needed

48:02.914 --> 48:05.606
- Pearl, Jack, smile.
[people chattering]

48:05.641 --> 48:06.884
Awesome.

48:06.918 --> 48:09.541
All right, gimme
your serious face.

48:09.576 --> 48:10.888
[chuckles]

48:10.922 --> 48:11.750
That's really good, right.

48:11.785 --> 48:13.614
- Yeah.
- Yeah, awesome.

48:13.649 --> 48:14.892
Hey, go find Katie.

48:14.926 --> 48:16.755
She's over by the
chocolate fountain.

48:16.790 --> 48:19.379
She's had her face
tattooed by a gypsy woman.

48:19.413 --> 48:20.932
And gimme one more.

48:23.417 --> 48:24.246
Hey, buddy.

48:24.280 --> 48:26.938
Ah, Pearl looks great, huh?

48:26.973 --> 48:28.560
What are the odds
you could be her dad?

48:28.595 --> 48:30.735
- Yeah, what are the odds?

48:30.769 --> 48:31.909
- How you doing, buddy?

48:31.943 --> 48:33.289
- Fine, Marty.

48:33.324 --> 48:34.739
I'm changing.

48:34.773 --> 48:36.637
- Yeah, yeah, I
know, they called me.

48:36.672 --> 48:38.398
I told 'em you'd be a natural.

48:38.432 --> 48:41.608
- [sighs] I'm still
a filmmaker, Marty.

48:41.642 --> 48:43.058
- Yeah, of course
you are, buddy.

48:43.092 --> 48:44.059
I mean, shit they bet a
little bit on the last one,

48:44.093 --> 48:46.578
but just let it blow over.

48:46.613 --> 48:48.442
Disney's got a
very short memory.

48:48.477 --> 48:50.928
[camera clicking]

48:50.962 --> 48:52.481
- Thanks, Marty.

48:52.515 --> 48:54.103
And it was Warners.

48:55.622 --> 48:56.485
- Pearl?

48:56.519 --> 48:58.418
Oh my God, hi!

48:58.452 --> 49:00.075
You have to get
your face painted.

49:00.109 --> 49:01.766
Harper, gimme the chair.

49:01.800 --> 49:03.250
Can you paint Kate on her arm?

49:03.285 --> 49:05.114
K-A-T-E.

49:06.115 --> 49:08.946
[birds chirping]

49:15.159 --> 49:17.816
[gentle music]

49:20.026 --> 49:22.649
[Pearl crying]

49:52.575 --> 49:53.507
- You okay?

49:57.339 --> 49:58.167
It's okay.

50:02.689 --> 50:05.174
Let's get outta here, come on.

50:15.184 --> 50:16.013
Uh...

50:17.221 --> 50:18.498
There's one that's like a thong

50:18.532 --> 50:21.397
but that doesn't
seem right to me.

50:21.432 --> 50:22.950
Mini, maxi, wings.

50:25.367 --> 50:27.679
Eve, stop yelling.
[people chattering]

50:27.714 --> 50:28.508
Yeah, I got it.

50:28.542 --> 50:29.785
It's 28, right?

50:31.545 --> 50:33.375
All right, it's got 36.

50:33.409 --> 50:34.341
Okay, great.

50:34.376 --> 50:37.689
[stammers] Thank you, thank you.

50:37.724 --> 50:40.623
[door bell chiming]

50:44.110 --> 50:45.352
- [Pearl] Did you
get the right ones?

50:45.387 --> 50:46.181
- Yep.
- You're sure.

50:46.215 --> 50:47.182
You called Nana?

50:47.216 --> 50:48.217
- [Jack] Yes.

50:55.121 --> 50:57.226
Just tell me you're okay.

51:00.574 --> 51:01.575
Listen, if you tell
me you're okay,

51:01.610 --> 51:02.887
I'll leave you alone.

51:02.921 --> 51:05.717
- [Eve] Tell your father
I said he's an idiot.

51:05.752 --> 51:07.064
- I can hear you, Eve.

51:07.098 --> 51:08.927
- She's 15 years old.

51:10.101 --> 51:11.723
Did you at least
get her the pads?

51:11.758 --> 51:13.208
- Yes.

51:13.242 --> 51:14.554
She's taking a bath.

51:14.588 --> 51:16.935
- I know she's taking a bath.

51:18.282 --> 51:20.249
And no, I am not drunk.

51:21.285 --> 51:22.217
- [Jack] Why not?

51:22.251 --> 51:23.908
- [Eve] I'm eight days sober.

51:23.942 --> 51:25.392
- Ah, you finally
joined a program.

51:25.427 --> 51:26.566
Mazel tov.

51:26.600 --> 51:28.257
- [Eve] One day at a time.

51:29.948 --> 51:32.951
You never thought about her
getting her period, did ya?

51:32.986 --> 51:34.436
- Why would I?

51:34.470 --> 51:37.784
- You're parenting
a teenage girl.

51:37.818 --> 51:38.647
Asshole.

51:43.445 --> 51:44.756
Call me tomorrow.

51:44.791 --> 51:46.758
- Thanks, Nana.

51:46.793 --> 51:49.106
And thanks for getting sober.

51:52.799 --> 51:54.801
- Now, I'm choosing to believe
that you're a strong person

51:54.835 --> 51:59.633
who will survive this because
of your ultimate resilience.

52:01.635 --> 52:04.121
[tense music]

52:06.813 --> 52:09.609
- [Pearl] Did he
do that with you?

52:09.643 --> 52:10.782
- All right.

52:10.817 --> 52:13.785
- Try to show his
feelings through movies?

52:13.820 --> 52:15.787
I don't care about his
movies or his lame attempts

52:15.822 --> 52:17.686
to teach me about life.
[people chattering]

52:17.720 --> 52:19.619
His movies aren't real.

52:19.653 --> 52:20.482
I'm real.

52:36.360 --> 52:37.844
You can't see me.

52:42.849 --> 52:43.677
- 4.4.

52:45.852 --> 52:46.853
Miss Rosen.

52:47.854 --> 52:48.648
- Yes, sir.

52:48.682 --> 52:50.167
- Am I boring you?

52:50.201 --> 52:51.375
- No, sir.

52:51.409 --> 52:53.308
- Your posture would
imply otherwise.

52:53.342 --> 52:54.999
- It's not you,
sir, but the lesson.

52:55.033 --> 52:55.931
- Too easy?

52:58.036 --> 52:58.761
Hmm.

53:00.349 --> 53:01.695
Jack spends half

53:03.041 --> 53:05.527
his weekly allowance on candy.

53:07.218 --> 53:10.048
To earn more money, his
parents let him wash

53:10.083 --> 53:12.189
the car for $4.

53:12.223 --> 53:17.021
How much is the weekly allowance
if he ended up with $11.

53:17.055 --> 53:17.884
- $14.

53:19.610 --> 53:21.370
- Please demonstrate.

53:52.746 --> 53:55.784
- 96 students went
on a field trip.

53:55.818 --> 53:57.234
Four buses were filled.

53:57.268 --> 53:59.408
Eight students took a car.

54:01.583 --> 54:04.413
How many students
filled each bus?

54:07.140 --> 54:07.968
- 22.

54:09.970 --> 54:12.456
Do you want me to demonstrate?

54:14.009 --> 54:16.080
[bell ringing]

54:16.114 --> 54:17.978
[students chattering]
- Thank you, students.

54:18.013 --> 54:19.325
Have a nice day.

54:20.602 --> 54:22.811
Uh, Miss Rosen, one minute.

54:31.440 --> 54:35.341
[door clattering and creaking]

54:45.454 --> 54:46.283
- Hey.

54:46.317 --> 54:47.629
- Hey.

54:47.663 --> 54:49.320
- What Filsoufi want?

54:49.355 --> 54:50.770
- I hurt his feelings.

54:50.804 --> 54:51.943
- What?

54:51.978 --> 54:53.462
- He told me not to
make him look foolish.

54:53.497 --> 54:54.981
- What'd you say?

54:55.015 --> 54:56.672
- I'm sorry, Mr. Filsoufi.

54:56.707 --> 54:59.434
[both laughing]

54:59.468 --> 55:00.297
- You going home?

55:00.331 --> 55:01.436
- Yeah.

55:01.470 --> 55:03.610
- You live with your dad, huh?

55:03.645 --> 55:04.508
- How did you know that?

55:04.542 --> 55:05.888
- I googled you.

55:06.855 --> 55:09.133
Read about your ma.

55:09.167 --> 55:11.204
I bet she was a righteous bitch.

55:11.238 --> 55:12.619
- She wasn't a bitch.

55:12.654 --> 55:13.793
- No.

55:13.827 --> 55:15.346
You could tell
she was a good ma.

55:15.381 --> 55:16.796
- How can you tell?

55:16.830 --> 55:17.969
- 'Cause you coulda
turned out to be

55:18.004 --> 55:20.213
a snotty rich little
ho but you ain't.

55:20.247 --> 55:22.629
That's your ma's doing.

55:22.664 --> 55:23.527
- Yeah.

55:23.561 --> 55:25.667
She was a righteous bitch.

55:25.701 --> 55:26.875
They put you back?

55:26.909 --> 55:28.359
- What do you mean?

55:28.394 --> 55:30.327
- Like, when you transferred,
they put you back a grade?

55:30.361 --> 55:31.155
- No.

55:31.189 --> 55:33.226
- Ah, so you a smarty.

55:33.260 --> 55:34.469
[both laughing]

55:34.503 --> 55:36.816
- You're a smarty
too, street smarty.

55:36.850 --> 55:37.989
[both laughing]

55:38.024 --> 55:39.336
[speaking in foreign language]

55:39.370 --> 55:41.648
[people laughing and chattering]

55:41.683 --> 55:43.063
Head down, chica.

55:47.413 --> 55:48.379
You're shitting me.
[lively music]

55:48.414 --> 55:49.760
$65 for a movie?

55:50.899 --> 55:53.177
My brother can get
you anything for free.

55:53.211 --> 55:54.005
- Pirating.

55:54.040 --> 55:54.834
- No.

55:54.868 --> 55:56.387
He gets 'em for free.

55:56.422 --> 55:57.664
- He steals them.

55:57.699 --> 55:59.528
- Only rich people
think like that.

55:59.563 --> 56:01.530
- I'm not rich anymore.

56:03.118 --> 56:04.533
♪ I used to think

56:04.568 --> 56:05.845
♪ I was

56:05.879 --> 56:06.742
- Hello [speaking in
foreign language].

56:06.777 --> 56:08.226
♪ I ain't alone no more

56:08.261 --> 56:09.849
- Hey, Perlita.

56:09.883 --> 56:11.402
- This is my friend Silvia.

56:11.437 --> 56:12.403
That's Zack.

56:13.300 --> 56:14.509
- [Zack] Hey there.

